Rating: 4
This was excellent. I'm teaching myself to cook, and even I was able to manage this one. I'm not a huge fan of cooked fruit, so the trick of this recipe is not to over sauté the fruit before putting it in the oven. I also used a very flavorful apple, a honeycrisp, as suggested. As a side, I sautéd a few slices of polenta in the same pan used to brown the chicken and sauté the apples. I think it could have used a bit more Stilton, but I'm a big Stilton fan.

