Rating: 4
This dish is AWESOME and really easy! I've made it several times. Tonight I pan seared the chicken cutlets, put them on a plate while I sautéed the apples until they were deep golden brown. I then added the chicken back to the pan with the apples all around and some on top of the chicken, splashed in some pear brandy (or sherry or any light wine) and covered it with gorgonzola cheese and let it simmer for a few minutes, uncovered. No need to heat the oven. It made an incredible sauce. Would have preferred stilton but it's not easy to get here; any sort of blue veined cheese works. LOVE IT!

Rating: 4
This dish is SO GOOD and easy to make! We made a sauce by frying up Pancetta, putting it to the side, and then added garlic, white wine, chicken broth, and butter to the pan to top the chicken off. I will make this next time we have company - it's so elegant and yummy.

Rating: 4
I anticipate this is a recipe I will make again and again. You can't beat the ease of this dish, especially when considering the end result. Of course, I'm also a huge Stilton fan. I used dried rosemary, and it worked, but I would use fresh next time. Paired it with sauteed delicata squash and beet parsley salad for a delightful and colorful fall meal.

